project_descr:
RP OUTCOME 2: Addressing poverty and inequalities through more inclusive and sustainable development pathways 
STRATEGIC PLAN 2018-2021, OUTCOME 1: Advance poverty eradication in all its forms and dimensions

outputs.output_descr: Output 2.1. Government approaches strengthened across the region to integrate the 2030 Agenda, the Paris Agreement, Sendai, and international/regional human rights and other agreements in development plans and budgets

Output 2.2. Regional innovative solutions for integrated and gender responsive social protection and care services to promote access to basic services, sustainable jobs and livelihoods for vulnerable groups.
Output 2.4 Regional awareness, advocacy and partnerships on corruption prevention strengthened contributing to enhanced integrity of national and sub-national institutions and systems

Output 2.6. Regional/sub-regional standards and practices enable evidence-based sustainable urbanization and local development, through smart cities and delivery of innovative and responsive public services, including for marginalized and key populations
Output 2.7: Gender equality tools and guidance aiming at advancing women's empowerment developed and tested and disseminated in public and private entities
